description:
&lt;p&gt;There has never been a more exciting time to join Acute Medicine at Russell’s Hall Hospital. First class staff are our best asset and recent investment is allowing us to expand our nursing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we can welcome you to our dynamic and highly skilled team. No day is the same in our fast paced unit and we really are the front door to the NHS. Full training will be provided for the right candidate including Trust induction and a supernumery period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will offer the Band 5 Staff nurse an opportunity to develop insight into Acute Medical Care. Throughout the 12 month programme the successful candidate will rotate between AEC, Rapid Assessment , and the AMU beds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will allow the candidate to gain exposure and experience in advanced nurse practice, assessment, triage and leadership. With structured support and education the candidate will develop the knowledge and skills needed to aid career progression in Acute medicine. The appointable candidate must have completed preceptorship in an acute care setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Acute Medical Unit has capacity for 70 patients including with each trained nurse responsible for between 6-8 patients supported by clinical support workers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Ambulatory Emergency Care Team work closely to support patients in assessment and treatment to be discharged where possible the same day&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameClaire WeatherstoneJob titleDeputy MatronEmail addressclaire.weatherstone@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
